content: Gotta be the best adventure game on the playstore
Game itself is fun but not as G-Rated as I was expecting. It has a lot of adult themes, war, murder, spying, theft, same sex relationships, and more. Probs not for kids.
getting started
Love it. So replayable. Works offline. Great stories.
Unique game
This is an amazing game. There's so much unique dialogue and diverse conversations you can have with the people you meet. It actually feels like you're traveling the world.
Dull.. Idea is nice but gameplay is boring I'm afraid.
Fantastic game - desparate for another like it!
Great interactive novel with replayability for several walkthoughs.

Instant classic. I honestly expected very little from this game. Instead it literally had me on the edge of my seat after a 2 week delay in east Asia, a 1 week detour in the Pacific (in which I pirated a ship), and 1 week detour in the Caribbean (getting kidnapped by pirates (seriously)). I ended up making it on day 79 with an extremely lucky final 3 days. I see almost infinite replay value due to 1000s of potential routes and player choices that directly affect the storyline.

This is a really fun game for those of us who like to read good, interesting stories. Think of this as an excellent interactive novel, and not so much as a video game. You play a French butler in the employ of an eccentric English gentleman who must win a bet to travel around the world in 80 days. The game makes the most sense if you embrace that role: you are responsible for everything, including keeping your master comfortable, managing funds and deciding itinerary

Outstanding choose-your-own adventure, probably the best game I've ever played on mobile. Wonderful writing and world-building, lots of replay value, nice visuals and sound. Dragging items between suitcases can be awkward at times but that's the only little flaw. I wish there were more updates to download or buy, would be great to revisit this world.
Whenever I get a new phone, I always play through this game! It's perfect really, always a different story and so many adventures to have.
A quite enjoyable text based game. Played it twice through making different choices and it definitely changed the experience. I can see myself coming back to this from time to time
I do like the game, it is fun and slightly emmersive and takes some strategy but also lick. Honestly I'm only rating it 3 stars because it gets old pretty quick. Other than that it's a good game.

(Ever read the Choose Your Own Adventure books? This is the game!) I didn't like this game at first. But I'm used to linear games where my choices don't really matter and the outcome of the game is the same for every player. But in 80 days, every action has a consequence and each subsequent option is based on those choices made before. I am coming back after playing the Sorcery! series and recommend those if you enjoy this game!

The game is amazing. Even though it has quite simple mechanics, the authors did a decent job to keep a player engaged from the beginning to the very end of a journey. By far I have completed the game several times, but I nearly covered all the possible scenarios, so I am carrying on. Very good game indeed. Have it on both PC and my phone. Thank you!
Great game. The English is complicated, though - for me who's not a native - and I couldn't find a place to switch to my mother language. But the experience is incredible.
Great game! Rearranging your suitcases is tricky, but other than that this is just as good as the PC version.
This game is amazing and btw I beat the game in 70 days and also in 64 (via the north pole)
No instructions, just starts and good luck you'll have done something wrong before you even know it was possible.
To this day 80 days remains a masterpiece

It's pretty fun and a novel concept for a game. I enjoyed playing and won first time in about 72 days, whilst there is some strategy it's not hardcore - the game is mostly about the story and quite relaxing to play which tbf is pretty unusual. There was some fun dialog and some interesting stuff happened but I was ready for it to be over by the end. I got it on play pass and it's short for a fiver but you could replay by taking a different route which I'm sure I will do at some point

A agreeble surprise that brought me back into fond memories from the 80s reading and re-reading Jules Verne's classics at my grandma in his native Nantes, visiting the museum wielding his name, a visit imbued with the smell of Petit LU cookies as their factory was right across the Loire from the museum.... The game itself is an excellent example of a modern take on IF. I failed my first attempt at the wager, finishing in 90 days, and immediately starting my second and successful in 75 days...
It's remarkable how well-executed this game is.. Since there are so many variations in paths you can take to accomplish your goal, there are many available options for replayability.

Love this game! I have a blast finding my way around the world. The contraptions are the best part. Who wouldn't love cities that walk, and trains that turn into submarines. You really let us embrace the wonder of Jules Verne. Thanks.
A fantastic text-based adventure, there's always something new to find in each playthrough.
Great story telling
Amazing game with a very original game loop. Can't stop circumnavigating the world!
Really enjoyable! Loved the steampunk update to the story, a nice surprise. Lots to explore surprisingly replayable as well to visit different cities and try different things.

Fun idea but too easy - I have played this through twice, the first time I did it in 72 days, the second in 63 days. I really like the idea but it isn't challenging enough to make it satisfying! I also find the suitcases really difficult to navigate - whilst trying to move things they keep closing because the swiping isn't calibrated well.
An excellent experience. The gameplay and graphics are so well done and the storylines are thoroughly enjoyable.
Controls are stupid.

This game was pretty fun, it took a couple of playthroughs to get under 80, the different encounters were unexpected and fun. I also love the background story of the automatons, especially the living ones in the Caribbean. I hope new content gets added, I'd love a list at the end of different stats, most used outfit, total number of finished sets, etc. Achievements could be neat too. Do women valets exist? An option to choose gender with different dialogue cards and outcomes could be fun too.

Great game! Absolutely fantastic! When I downloaded the game, I thought it's just circumnavigating the globe and money management but holy cow there's a whole freaking lore in here. And some people probably give bad reviews because some vehicles are weird but they simply don't get that it's steampunk alternate reality. Sure, the control's a bit rough but you'll get used to it eventually. Btw I managed to get around the world in 48 days and right now playing some more to understand the lore
Nice UI, Nice Story Writing , one of the best mobile games i've ever tried

Great game, be great if it was sims style characters with 3d travel but that would be epic coding to do lol. Maybe one day someone will make a real earth or historic 3d adventure with journey options.
Seemingly an opportunity for diversification!
Love the story and the steampunk style. Looking forward to seeing what else this team comes up with.
This game is pretty fun. Its hard beware of the north is all i will say. Winter is coming
Fun game. Interesting world and characters. Good replayability for the money as there are soo many routes to take. There some strangeness to discover as it's set in a steampunk version of the novel.
Adiaforo
A game i keep coming back to

This is perhaps one of my favourite mobile games, and the one that showed me they could be much more than bad microtransaction-filled garbage. Would also be great for people who don't play many games, as it's effectively a slightly more in depth choose your own adventure book, with all the reading that goes with that. Fantastic art style, high replayability, and very well written.
Genuinely fun game with a bit of replayability. Played it through a few times and enjoyed it.
Wow, what a rubbish game. I'm surprised someone would actually pay Â£4.99. Plenty of mugs in the world!

I just finished my second gameplay, and it was just as fun the second time. I was skeptical because I've found other cyoa games I've downloaded to be boring and slightly misogynistic, so I was pleasantly surprised by this game. I liked that players have to make decisions quickly, it made the game feel exciting but not stressful. There were a few game mechanics that could have been improved, but I still found it to be a fun game with a lot of replayability.
I've never seen a game on any platform that can be replayed this many times and offer a consistently new experience
Support decent mobile gaming with your money and buy this app. The game is immersive and replayable.
Smart and interesting and funny and totally uninterested in profits, gambling or addicting people. I have no idea what this game is doing on mobile, but for the love of God, buy it while you can!
Reccomend for any Jules Verne fans
Good fun.!
Error at the start with retry button, not working
Most good mobile games are "good... for a mobile game." This game is just good.
Absolutely love this one. So much replay value! Keep coming back to it. Wonderfully engaging and chill experience playing it
Eh
Kick arse game!

Fun adventures, and after my 4th game I understood - anything can happen, I would sudgest some save option, maybe not unlimited but for example 3 savestates per game or so, thou I understand lack of them aswell - in real adventure you don't really have savestates. But great game, well done, I imagine how nice would be to play thru other Jules Verne books inspired games similar to this one

It was really easy to skip too much, or mess up. What I got from players that succeeded was that it mostly came down to luck regarding routes and items. I had many chances to play it free with playpass and it always disappointed.
Played it for free with Google play pass. I was considering buying in it until I noticed there's been no updates for over a year!

Freaking fantastic...my quickest time ws 26 days...i cheated and went north lol.....but i went alllll the way around 5xs lol...great game good graphics and hilarious humor...i loved it and we need a part 2 google.....FIRST ONE TO CENTER EARTH AND BACK...

This was a great game. So far Ive played it all the way through twice. Each time was a completely different story altogether. If you like text adventure games at all I promise you will enjoy this one for the interesting characters and plots full of twists. That being said, I think this game is worth playing even if you arent a fan of text games. I got just as much enjoyment picking different paths to travel and managing your characters recources. This game is well worth the money spent.

I agree with others Players Reviews that the Text is Really wooden. I found myself skim reading a lot of it. The characters were both 1 dimensions l. The choices were limited. That said, I initially enjoyed the premise of the game; but got bored of it, took a long break, and took weeks to "feel" like playing again. I really hated the tedium of the traveling times and often making boring conversation along the journey with characters who were completely irrelevant to the story/game.

Quite how you turn a rollicking Victorian adventure novel into a game so wearily slow and tedious while also stripping the two main characters of their joie de vivre is quite beyond me. The script is unbearably wooden compared to Verne's original, the Steampunk additions strike me as superficial, the game mechanics seem clunky, and I have had more fun auditing my accounts. Around the World in 80 Years, more like. I play games to escape from tedium, not to be embraced by it. What even?
What a great concept! I've played it a few times through already.
Quality game. Took me a few goes to beat it. Love how you cn end up anywhere in the world.

Great experience. I was a bit surprised in the beginning when I saw that the world is SiFi, but the creators integrated perfectly the new world into the realities of the 19th century. As a down size I finished twice in under 70 days even though I had been delayed on the way multiple times or take detours on purpose to make profit. Maybe the creators should increase the difficulty to be more challenging.
Truly an amazing and beautiful game.

I was rather excited to play this game, having enjoyed the novel it's based on as a child. Sadly, the way the developers have chosen to restrict the player's decisions, not allowing one to go back at any point, when mistakes are easily made and options are terribly limited, completely ruins the experience, for me. The music and visual style capture the spirit of the journey wonderfully, but having to restart each time one makes an error is preposterously frustrating. What a silly waste of time!
Excepcional game!

This game is excellent. Like those old choose your ending books. It took me a week of playing it for a few hours each night, to finish one ending and I loved every second of it. Highly recommend it for every book lover.
Very enjoyable
Hard but fun

I tried playing this game but It wasn't really the type of game I normally play. I didn't get very far and realized that the text format wasn't the platform i liked. If the game was a mmorpg with illustrations I would like it more. However for a text based game it was one of the more exciting text styled games. Don't get me wrong I prefer image based games but this wasn't that bad. The texts were fairly enjoyable for texts and the graphics were basic. If i had to pay I would pass.
Unimpressed..I thought it could have been abit more adventurous...just a click game to read..not cool
Well done
Beautiful game
Interesting enough the first few go rounds, but very little replay value after that.
Not quite a storytelling game or a text adventure, but a beautiful world to explore. Highly recommend.

I thought this game would stick to experiences of the contemporary world. Learning about the world is what drew me to the game in the first place. But it has funny things such as moving cities and what not. I thought the makers would take thorough care in ensuring that everything is drawn from the real world. Sadly, that's not the case. Also, finished the game in first go. Down voting to 1 star to draw attention.
Had a lot of fun with this one, would recommend
Bleh.

It is an unusual things when a mobile game surprises you, but 80 Days has succeeded in doing such with me. The mechanics are relatively simple, but they come together to create incentive to experiment in regards to journeys- and considering there are more than 100 cities the room to experiment is vast. However, the true reason to buy this game is the writing- for it manages to condense the essence of RPG storytelling down in a way that surpasses many larger RPGs.

Pros: beautiful animation and music. Creative storytelling. Many plots. Free game. Funny and witty. Excellent ending if you win. Cons: racist portrayal of Burmese, Chinese, French and Filipino people. Classist. Prejudiced against unmarried and childless people. Main character is bullied if he voices any complaints or unhappiness. Game now uninstalled from my phone.

Game is crazy addicting. Imagine the best choose your adventure book, throw in some spontaneous events, and a whole lot of strategy. I've played through at least 10 times and I'm still going back for more.
Had a lot of fun in the first hour, I expect many more. No ads, good use of Google Rewards!
I didn't like this game at all. I would like to get refunded for it. It's really boring, uninstalled it after less than a day
Not the same 80days i was looking for

I would rate it better but you should go where you please with your master every time in a country always saying route yo London everytime I say we ain't heading anyway it still have route to London noting just because 80 days past want you to return home fixed when I ready go back to London I will be waiting on airship

Initially was enamored because of the beautiful chiaroscuro graphics but the writing gets redundant over time. No exciting payoff to rehashing the stories numerous times as the character choices all seem the same with more or less the same consequences. Bad purchase :(
A fantastic game. It was so tense even though the gameplay was slow it felt fast and energetic.
i want a refund please it wont open and i just payed 5 pound please get back kind regards raye houghton
This is a great game and it has a great concept. It is quite unique and every time you play it it will be quite different. I love it.

Really love this game! It has engaging writing and the characters are lovely too. Before, I thought the play time per round will be rather short but it is actually not! Beside, one route could differ a lot from another so it keep us away from being bored. So far I have played two times but there are still around many unexplored cities to be seen! Such an amazing game. I literally have no complaints.

Verne would be proud.
Ok. Too many unknowns. If we sell maps do we lose routes? Why can't we visit all places? Why can't we backtrack? Once we collect a set do we have to keep it to have the bonuses from them?
Fun game.
Great text based game in a steampunk setting. Its got good management gameplay, as you have to juggle your health your boss's health and hsppiness, food, money.
Pretty nice game well in story and satisfied me
Excellent story, fantastic game! But..moving items between suitcases is clunky and I keep missing transport because of this. PLEASE FIX!!!
It's sort of glitched out when I first opened it, but once I restarted it, I loved it this game! Fun combination of choose your own adventure and survival. Extremely high replay value!

For a narrative, it is actually pretty good. The goal seems pretty clear. Their are a few different dialogue options to choose from which is nice. Personally, not a mega huge fan, but overall it is good. I would recommend this.

I just started playing and I love this game. It is a wonderful text based game with a steampunk theme. It is really immersive and you get into character so easily. I still haven't finished it but will continue to edit this so I can review it when I'm done. So far it's really fun! Edit: WOW this game was great! I made it around the world in 64 days! There's so many choices to make so many cities to visit and although I didn't visit them all I want to play again so I can. 10/10 will play again!
Not at all worth the money.
Boring and too wordy.
Astonishing breadth of content and beauty in every little touch.

It's like a choose your own adventure book in modern form. I found it very enjoyable and binge worthy. A must if you're a bibliophile and enjoy geography, history, and/or steampunk. Lovely work, developers! My record is 54 days after several tries ;)
The only complaint I have is that moving items from one suitcase to another is clunky and often results in missing transportation. Other than that I love this game! Please make a sequel!
Linear and repetitive. Disappointing.
This game was boring no fun I tried to get into it but I just couldn't this game sucks

Absolutely amazing. So many cities to visit, so many paths to take, and people to talk to, and items to trade! And I love that even should you fail your trip, you don't get a "you lost" screen but rather get to finish your trip, and try again. I wish, though, that the game would let you drop it and pick up at any time. Right now, the game only gets saved at cities, so you lose progress if you close the game in the middle of travelling between cities.

Amazing game with a great story line. I love replaying after completing because of the different choices and routes. I just wish you could maybe keep a discovered route or have some bonus from completing the game beforehand.
This is good. Even though I've forgotten most of the original story, I found myself taken on an equally exciting journey. Missed by a few days, damn.
This game is incredible - some of the deepest and most fascinating world building I've ever encountered - ENDLESS and fascinating possibilities, and a stay-up-late-playing DELIGHT.

Easily one of the best written, quirky, and fun games I've played in recent memory. You take the role of Passepartout, valet and serviceman to Phineas Fogg, a London aristocrat, who has wagered with his cohorts that he can cross the globe in eighty days. As you travel the world, you'll be building friendships, trading goods, and trimming one or two eyebrows! This game isn't afraid to throw you off course and take you for an unexpected ride- how much of it you'll enjoy is up to player preference.
Beautiful game! Compelling story with fun mechanics.
My favorite app by far. Multiple levels of story and fun; challenges and twists. Will there be a sequel?
This is an amazing game/app, I was surprised and happy with it entirely. ðŸ‘

Boring you'll be reading their story across the globe for 80 days of nothing. Unless you want to read a non story of travel gibberish. Ok if it was like 2 bucks and i dont mind paying for games. But for 6 bucks blah

The controls are a bit rough. Your game is time based. You have to prepare suitcases and switching items to other suit cases is hard to do. So sometimes you miss a flight,ship,ect.. Because you can't move your items easily. Makes it frustrating because of the controls. You look on the map and it is super sensitive and hard to navigate. The game is enjoyable but the controls really impact your experience.

Waste of money. I was under the impression that this was a game. In actuality, this is a book with different paths depending on which "choices" you make. You aren't deciding anything, you get to pick between 3-5 different things based on the first few words.. You don't even know what you are picking. Because I paid for it, I tried to stick it out and follow along but it was so boring it couldn't keep my interest. There is zero gameplay in this game(Book). Can I please have my money back?
Boring. More of a text based choose your own adventure book from the 1980s than a game.
Oh my geez i played this game all afternoon n evening! Im so hooked! So much fun!!!ðŸ˜
Really fun and addictive. Immerse yourself into unique stories based on the decisions / routes you take, or just dash around the world in the midst efficient way possible.

I just got done bing playing this for nearly 2 hours. Needless to say, quite a good game! Gives me the feeling of actually travelling. There seems to be tons of replayability as well, as I've only visited a few of the cities possible!
Wonderful !!! I can escape my appartment and go on the best vacation of my life. . . Well worth the money!!Â° Thank you for your amazing Company !!!
Entertaining!

A fabulous game, with a deep story to explore. I'm on my fourth play through so far, and each time has been dramatically different. There's a whole world that you only catch glimpses of, rewarding you for digging deeper. My only complaint is that some of the controls are a little touchy (moving things around suitcases can be tough, for example) but this is a minor hiccup on an otherwise great game. Well worth the cost.
I can't open the game after the download was completed...it is stuck, help me
Highly Educational! Hours and days of fun.

The breadth of the game and the experience it delivers in as little as three hours is stunning. The writing is excellent, the rhythm perfect. In my first playthrough, I helped an infiltrating spy, paid fishermen to sneak in a military city, was caught and jailed, climbed on top of a zeppelin, had to run with slavers through Africa to barely make it back in time. Exhilarating.
What an adventure.. aaamazing

Lacks replay value after 3 or 4 trips, but is seriously one of the best original experiences I've had on mobile. If you're in the mood for a short strategy time/inventory management game with fun and quirky dialogue that immerses you into the journey, 80 Days is for you.
One of the more gratifying mobile games I've played. Love the writing. It definitely is reminiscent of the novel.

I can't say much without spoiling the game. However be it the start of your first journey or twentieth there is always more too see. Just when you think you've done most of what the game offers it'll suprise you. I also have to mention the wonderful sound that brings the game to life . It makes you feel as if you were really there. All in all this is a gem and I'd definitely recommend it.
Awesome gamplay/ book dynamic Def buy

Awesome ðŸ‘
Best thing for me is the replayability. Wish there was a way to track the unique encounters I've had. Favorite game I've played for a phone.

I have played this for hours and hours, and I have not yet run out of things to discover. Little parts of this crazy, steampunk alternate history come out in each playthrough, and I'm always ready for the next little nugget of story.

Marvelous experience. The graphics are nice and clean, with a really cool steampunk aesthetic. The choices/routes you can take are many, and so this game needs quite a lot of (unique) playthroughs if you want to see all it has to offer. Superb writingâ€”greatly engaging, and it does encourage you to play through the game many times to see all of its possible routes. Overall, I really recommend getting this game.

Extrodinary game. 3 replays, 2-3 hours each. None was the same. Eventually there will be some repetition, Im sure. However Ive gotteb such a deep and fufilling story. Its incredible how naturally connected the options feel.
A very well presented and entertaining choose your own adventure
This game needs a save feature. Close the app for even a second and you can be sent backwards 15minutes. I've played the same part over because I didn't have time to finish

Gets frustrating! I've just spent ages planning and travelling, only to accidentally sell an item on the market because the wrong suitcase was in the middle, and it's totally blown my onwards plans! Really can't be bothered starting again!

Hands down one of the best mobile games I have ever played. This game is worth every penny. Fantastic story, amazing depth, and great world building. It has so much replayability as it is a vastly different story every time. 95% of mobile games these days are utter trash, but this is one of those rare exceptions that doens't just deliver, but over-delivers. You will not regret buying this game. It makes me happy to see such a good game created for mobile users

For a near 6 year old game this really is one of the best around. Really fun to pass time. Only criticism is that it absolutely drains my battery on my S10+, and some form of sequel (I know a bit hard with a CYOA) would be great, I see you guys have other adventure games but something more in the style if 80 Days would be awesome!!
I truly enjoyed playing this game. The intricate detail in every aspect of the game is astounding!!! If it was a little cheaper I would purchase it...

Keeps dropping me off in the middle of my trips that I've already paid for. Paid 3700 for trans siberian trip but dropped me at Omsk leaving me broke. I like the idea of the game but there are too many problems with it.
Love it! Very replayable and did so countless times over the past year! Paris dialogue becomes repetitive and it would be nice if more dialouge could be added and perhaps a few more trading options.
Fun but kind of questionable being a dude and the game prompts you to make out with other dudes.
Great fun game, part adventure game part simulation. Figure out to cross the globe in 80 days. Had 2 play through and some fun encounters
Terrible. Just paid 5 quid and won't even open. Don't waste your money

Hands down the best mobile game currently on the market. Countless hours of OFFLINE, story driven entertainment. With extreme replayability. Whether a fan of games, jules verne, stories on general or all three, this game is a must have. Massively underpriced.
A good game but the only issue with it is that whenever I turn my phone off to do something else it restarts the game to the last city meaning I have to do all the choices again.
Really great cyoa game, though not for me specifically.
Good

So good, so calming, so replayable. If you wanted to go to the North Pole, start a ship mutiny, get stuck in Panama, capture Jesse James, ride the Nautillous, and find El Dolrado, you can do all of them here - if you pick the right choices at the right time!
Great choose your own story line

Pros: Unique, replayable, good graphics, challenging (difficult games are fun!) Cons: Make starting location random, not just London - to get around Fogg being British, maybe they're on holiday when they decide to take up the wager, secondly, I'd personally like more gameplay, less story. So maybe multiple ways of getting to the same destination with pros and cons. Lastly, don't allow travel with too many suitcases! Update: Please make the game harder, on my second playthrough I made it in 76.
Beautifully written and designed, huge replay possibilities, relaxing and inspiring. I still wish for more.
Excellent for learning geography.

Wonderful game that keeps you interested with lots to discover across a world that feels huge. Brilliant dialogue keeps you glued to the screen , with lots of replay value. Wonderful game. Can't recommend enough!
The world overview map is absolutely terrible to use. The game itself looks solid, just not my cup of tea.
Pretty amazing game. Seems like you can replay it 100 times and see completely different stuff
A beautiful text-based adventure. The variety of journey possibilities and excellent writing keep you playing.

My only issues were with the controls. Times I accidentally clicked on a selection that I hadn't meant to, but there was no way to go back. There were times I hadn't even read all the choices but just trying to scroll down to read them all and I had accidentally touched one of the choices and it moved on to another screen. Other than that, I enjoyed the story-line and played it twice...the second time I made it within 80 days. Hope there's more of these games with these characters!
Each play through is remarkably different!

I was skeptical when I first downloaded this, and I didn't quite understand the depth of it until I finished my first trip around the world. It has a ton of replayability, and an interesting story! I've played it 10 times or more
Excellent
Great game with a great story and many choices to make that will determine the outcome.
Nice and adictive

I keep coming back to this game over the years. Fun to explore all the possibilities. Well written and a cool aesthetic.

Great portrait game to play, with a lot of replayability and witty writing!

Not worth the money and wouldn't give a refund
I've never seen this much effort put into a mobile game, period. Absolutely phenomenal game and recommend it to all.
Excellent game that have played through countless times. Would recommend, best game you can play on your phone

It's worth playing once through but it is a bit too long-winded to be really fun. The management of suitcase inventory is a pain. Conversations with drivers etc are very poorly developed in most cases.

Actually pretty good for a text based game but while it's fun to "live" the old Jules Verne novel by yourself, I feel it gets repetitive after a while. I'm happy I played it (and managed to win my bet and go around the world in only 69 days) but once will be enough and I'll be uninstalling the game and probably will never play it again. But then again, who knows?

Great idea, execution only so-so. Far too easy to accidentally skip important dialogue opportunities, and the game isn't clear about too many things. That along with playthrough taking only about 2 hours makes it a no from me. I'm just glad I got to play it through subscription, not having paid full price for it.

I quite enjoy the game at first few rounds but it can get repetitive and I think there might be some design problems. I visited Thessaloniki and Athens first then go to Meteora Valley and now I'm stuck there with only sleep option... I guess we're not supposed to visit a place twice but then you shouldn't allow users to enter a dead end with no way out
One of the best Android games I have ever played. This game is fun, charming, and original.
I rarely give 5 star but this definitely deserves it. All I can say is wow. I just finished my play through and it was amazing. Get this game!

Excellent adventure game that will leave you wishing you could race around the world in steampunk style. A few replays and you suddenly learn what cities to avoid to reduce repetition, but with so many routes, you have options.
How is this even a game? Lmao
A great game
Great concept, can be a little slow at times, UI can also be a little finicky. Really great game though.

This is really well written. I can get lost in the story for hours on end. Its very immersive. Makes you feel like you're actually traveling and exploring these cities. Highly recommend for anyone who enjoys adventure and reading.

One of the most compelling interactive fiction games I've played on any platform. The stories, and there are so many, are beautiful, funny, heart-warming, compelling, and memorable. The loop of the game, travelling between cities and countries and continents, purchasing goods, chatting with folk, taking in the scenery, and contemplating life as a simple valet, is a seamless experience. Once a bedtime story, now a seemingly-endless tale I can take with me anywhere, I cannot recommend this enough.

A wonderfully written cross between Choose Your Own Adventure and the Oregon Trail (were it posh Europeans in airships rather than pioneers with disease haha). Tons of routes and characters, and it's really compelling; the video game equivalent of a page-turner. Unfortunately, the animations are VERY slow, which is frustrating you're so eager for the story to process. If I could speed things up this would be a 5, but the glacial pace interrupts the experience enough to drag my score to a 3.
Brilliant, just amazing
Great game, oddly relaxing :)
Awesome game!
Storyline is great but not alot to interact with
Simply delightful. Whimsical. Fun.
Well written, intriguing, and constantly engaging. I normally delete useless games but this is more so a experience. Hope the developer create some more content like this.
Very bland. Much less interesting and enjoyable than reading a book of the same sort.
Absolutely superb. If you buy one game for your phone, make it this.
New Age Classic from the best old age.
This is a very good game

Don't purchase! Amazing graphics, gameplay, back story and idea. But can only be played once. Turns out to be ridiculously expensive for a one time 3 hour long game. Needs to have the option of chosing direction, and perhaps throwing in challenges of compulsory visiting certain cities to win the game. Lack of being able to play again or for a longer time makes this game quite pointless
graohics okay, but game interface im not a fan of
Wonderful game. Tons of replayability.

Everything I like in a game. Can be replayed many times with different results each time. I hope inkle comes out with more games like these, where it's about traveling and exploring.

Wow! I didn't expect this game to be as amazing as it is! This has easily become my favorite game. It's incredibly addicting, highly entertaining, and very well written. The writer did a fantastic job of capturing Verne's imagination and fusing it with a classic "pulp" adventure novel style. The only thing I would recommend to improve the app would be a way to review a summary of my previous trips around the world. This is an absolute GEM! You hit it out of the ballpark! :)
wish there was a single player mode where you can save your progress
excellent game.
great story board, you can choose you own route and play it multiple times. it improves your geographics knowledge and chance to knew places you might not be able to visit irl. LOL

This is a great game, I went around the world about 20 times, shortest time was 40 days completed. Trying different routes and making as much money as possible was fun as well, no matter how long it took. The text format is engaging, love the music and the choose-your-own-adventure format, which reminds me of those books from long ago. Some of the content though was pretty white-person-centric, I know it is the 1800s, but I was offended several times by some descriptions of people of color
like it alot

i am having a lot of fun playing this game. so many routes to take with many surprises and detours. dialogue/writing is top notch and well done i haven't made it in 80 days yet but i will. replayability is very high and this is a purchase i have not regretted.
not working, stuck on the download complete "lets go" screen. please fix or give me a refund

I wanted to get this game for years but never had the opportunity. Now, I've tried playing in twice, over a year apart, and it's been terrible both times. The social interactions lack depth, the random, thrown off course events make it very frustrating, and the saving system makes you lose tedious progress. As someone who loves choose your own adventures, this was a massive disappointment.
One or the best games I've ever played. Incredible novel brought to life through interactive choice based game play. I've played through it a dozen times now and it never gets old.
Game requires network connection for no good reason I can see

Replayability is great due to the variety of random choices available, but the inventory interface...ugh, it's really difficult to move items between suitcases, and by the looks of other reviews I can tell it's not just me. It really sucks. Great game otherwise.
I keep coming back!
Overall a very good game. Plenty of variation in storylines and sub-plots depending on the route you take.
I am mesmerized... The amount of work put behind such a marvellous masterpiece is unimaginable. Although there is scope for minor improvements but still this game is a must-play for all story lovers.
Probably the most interactive game I've ever played, within terrific graphics and algorithm to which player can choose any routes to be visited. Stunning.

I absolutely loved it, the world has an incredible atmosphere with an almost full steampunk vibe. I got to visit many cities around the world including my own, I found the character interactions very compelling with several intense unforgettable moments. I finished my first game in only 69 days as I raced across the Atlantic ocean after having to sell all my possessions. If I had any suggestions it would be to have different difficulties. Other than that I would gladly recommend it to anyone.
Fantastic! Vaguely reminiscent of the Oregon Trail from my youth
Great dialogs and playability, easily 4/5*.
Awesome Game. Managed to clear in 62 days. Like the others have said before me, luggage interface could use some tweaking
Good interactive novel.
Excellent text adventure. Intriguing and evolving scripts, several different paths routes and scenarios. Need more games from you guys!
Not sure how this got such high ratings. I was interested because it does not need to be online and figured it would keep me occupied during my plane travels. Lost 5 bucks... save your money.
Nicely done and stylized game. Probably me, but I find playing it to be rather dull. Uninstalling.

One, if not the, very best game on Android right now. Inkle studios hits all the right tunes with this adventure game. Every new game plays out differently and the game seems to be full of great little stories to tell. Seeing the adventure unfold in front of your eyes in such a beautiful way is something truly special. Thank you.

Inkle games are all awesome, but I like this one the best. If you like text based games, this is a no-brainer, and even if you don't, this might be the exception.
beautiful game. worth the money
a very fun game, insane replayability. Worth every penny

The writing in this game is wildly high calibre. I didn't expect it. Good job, folks. The replayability is also huge because not only are there so many different routes to take, but certain events happen if you leave at certain times and then on top of THAT there are 8 different seeds with whole different stories. Give the writer(s?) a raise.

such fun storytelling. so rich and intricate and so much to explore

great game
amazing

Gem of a game mixing interactive fiction with a travel game. Full of little surprises and hidden easter eggs too. UI is fiddly sometimes is my only mild complaint. But it's worth every penny.
Is anyone else really struggling with clicking the damn choice you wish to make? Horrible responsiveness of controls.. Shame since it ruins what seems to be a perfectly entertaining game
Honestly still the best mobile game I've played to this day. Great emergent story telling but really chill

Very pretty, but clunky inconsistent controls, and lack of important info in ui. It's weird that there's time pressure when planning routes, but not while on the road, and you can't make plans while on the road.
Just a grand old time

Fantastic title with no in-app purchases or wait times. Just finished my first play through and am very impressed with the CYOA aspect with inventory along the way. I did it in 74 days with two missed travel opportunities due to timing. Will play through again and try a different route knowing what I know now. Going through Canada was a great experience for my Suave character but I feel like South America is going to be quite a bit faster if I can go from Brazil to Portual on an Airship or something. To be determined. The writing is truly the star of the show here. Absolutely brilliant script.

Love this game!!!! Lots of storylines, multiple endings, and so much fun! Kudos on the diversity nod too. Love the gay love storyline. Well worth the money and great for long plane trips when the wanderlust hits you!

I'm already on my second journey and the story is different, the people you meet are different. Really a well done created game. Every penny is worth it for this game!
Just excellent. Reminds me of the old choose your own adventures

This is my favorite game that I have played in a very long time. Amazing interactive storytelling. Beautiful & appropriate score. Easy controls. Ready to learn. Great replayability. New options and routes appear in subsequent games after completion. So much steampunk fun!

Absolutely one of the best phone games out there. The writing is superb and

Really engaging, replayable game! You can take many routes, starting with 
the obvious route through Russia but as you deviate from this route the 
weirder and more inventive the landscape becomes. The sense of humour, 
evocative art and inventive characters and locations make for a really 
memorable, dream-like game. Highly recommend.

Unbelievably good! So many different branches to take story-wise, that I'm 
sure that a person could play this for 24 hours straight and still not have 
uncovered every event! Game is totally worth the price and is probably in 
the top ten Android games of all time.

Fantastic, i am addicted to finding new and faster routes and ive just

Beautiful graphics, a compelling story, and great writing already make this

One of the most satisfying purchase on Google play. A must buy, great game

"80 Days" represents the pinnacle of mobile gaming. It explores fully the 
capabilities of a smart phone that almost anyone can enjoy; it would be 
difficult to find a device incapable of running it decently enough. It's 
beautifully realized both graphically and narratively. The writing leaves 
nothing to be desired, and the sheer number of completely developed routes 
is impressive. It's engaging, humorous, and even touching. Best of all, 
it's very replayable. My only suggestion would be to add "superlatives" 
awarded at the journey's end to build upon the statistics, more than just 
"favorite mode of transport." A hearty congratulations to everyone who 
worked on this masterpiece.

The screenshots don't represent the game well enough. I hesitated from 
buying for quite some time but now that I finally did I can only recommend 
it. Every playthrough is different (I'm at 4 now), there are so many things 
to explore and the atmosphere is absolutely remarkable.

Hands down the best game I have purchased on Google Play. Seemingly endless

The best interactive fiction I've seen in a long time.

I like the story, the graphics and various characters you'll encounter on your round the world trip, very nice !!

An extraordinary example of interactive fiction. The quality and tone of the half-million word script is spot on, so much of the credit must go to the writer, Meg Jayanth. The replayability is outstanding: there is so much to discover in this richly-imagined steampunk world.  The single criticism I have is of the fiddly way that items must be moved between suitcases. This is a wonderful build your own adventure game. You will travel all around the globe, closely watching your time and finances in an effort to win the main challenge. But the charm of the game is the other things you can do along the way - you will solve murder mysteries, talk to robot guardians, go on sub quests, and have wonderful conversations! This is an all around fantastic experience.

replyContent: Hi Emily, sorry to hear it still isn't working properly for you. Can you open the game settings (cog icon at the top right), tap Send Feedback, then Attach Save Files? That will compose an email to us that includes some log files that may help track down the problem.

content: Imagine a few dozen really good choose-your-own-adventure books bundled into one beautiful, charming package that you can delve into from the comfort of your own phone.

What can I say, I boarded a walking city, fled from a city that was being sieged, saved a man's life which earned me a huge flying bird to take me to Beijing. I then set sail to San Francisco but halfway the captain decided to take us to Hawaii, we secretly got crew members on board a mutiny When we reached Hawaii, it failed and we were expelled from the ship, I then set sail to South America where I sailed to an island. I took path to new Orleans where I reached the 80 day mark and found a drinking den. I hopped on an airship on route to an Atlantic island, I convinced the captain to take us to London, he did however we crashed just off shore. Helicopters rescued us and we made it to London. Absolutely brilliant game!

Better than any choose your own adventure and mature enough for every adult. Each journey is unique and brings you back for more.
Such an awesome game!
Love the stories and all the different places to explore. A great game that never gets old!

Truly one of the best games released this decade. Full of 19th century atmosphere, but with a steam-punk twist on the Jules Verne classic. Like all truly great games, this gem has a simple premise and rules, but complex and engaging play. Spend some time with the romantic traveller in yourself: Download and play.
It gonna be better if it supports Chinese.
The failure in it is very realistic, and you can choose whatever path you want, you can also plan your adventures using your money, time, and Fogg's health as info. Do please download this game.
Charming as hell.

Absolutely the best. Every small choice matters in the end. The landscapes are beautiful, but the story is even more so.
amazing! So many ways you can play this game and so many choices you can make!

A classic

Interactive story telling done right. Beautiful to look at, and ridiculously well written. Beautifully executed steam punk retelling of the Verne classic, whose framing device was perfectly chosen. I hope inkle can find some more stories to tell in this wonderful manner. Bravo.
Absolutely loved this game! I've been a fan of Jules Verne's Around since I was a kid. This game allowed me to experience the wonder of reading Around the World in 80 Days

Absolutely love this game and could not go without it. It is absolutely my favorite game of all time. The artwork looks great and the writing is beatiful. The soundtrack is superb but for some reason the victory music doesn't play when I finish a game which really bothers me as I really enjoy it. Other than that though, fantastic game. I highly recommend it.

A very fun game to pass the time, and a very intricate story keeps you engrossed the entire time. The visuals are nothing spectacular, but it makes up for it in content. My only complaint would have to be about backtracking. I am a curious guy, and having over 100 destinations to visit, I wanna see them all..but you can't. Time and time again you will get locked into a city because you wanted to go off course, forcing you to restart. Add a function where in those cases, you can at least go back to the previous city so you don't need to start anew. Very frustrating. Fix this and it'll be a perfect game worthy of 5 stars.
Everything by inkle is top notch.
Phenomenal game. This is the best mobile game I have played.
Another win for inkle
Good game but too easy. Played it twice so far and finished it both times. Doesn't look like you can really lose if you watch your money and time.

Victory isn't guaranteed so decisions matter, and even failure results in an incredible ride. I've replayed this 3 times and every path is vastly different. If I had one complaint it might be that it's too difficult to put together clothing sets, and it doesn't feel worth it when you do.
Thank you Felicia Day for tweeting about this. I've played two rounds in 8 hours, it's magnificently addicting. I'd love to see more from this studio.

inkle Ltd can thank Felicia Day for my purchase of this game. Beautiful design and flow to this stylistic game! Very cool concept, and it's easy to lose hours while playing it. Make sure you're ready to do some reading, as that's the basis of the adventure!
Truly a masterpiece.
One of the best gaming experiences I've ever had!
An excellent game on its own merits, and also a great option for mobile devices. 80 Days is well worth the price.
An enjoyable way to read Around The World in 80 Days, with a twist!

Best purchase I've made in a long time. Really fun story with a ton of replayability. Highly recommended! Otherwise, no complaints!

Wow!!!! Finally a game which is complex enough to feel achievement when finishing, yet has not exhausted its content, so you can play time and again. The only game I've come across which I'll actually leave on my device so I can play it again.
Great adventure game presented simply but wonderfully. A top game to play on a commute to work out in the evening.
Fantastic game with a great UI and intuitive controls. Easy to play multiple times taking various routes and experiencing different stories.  Highly recommend for any Jules Verne fans!

A great adventure that succeees in the work it's based on in many more ways than one, telling some of our own modern woes in a story that Jules Verne would & did tell. It's truly a game anyone, gamer or not, should play.
Charming  collection  of weird steampunk short  stories
Grafik gut, Gameplay super, Story episch. Lob an die Entwickler ;)
I love the game im so happy it works on my phone again!!!
So so

This is one of my favourite games. As a game developer and also someone who wants to travel more it really struck a chord with me. The diy nature of your travels in this game really help you explore the universe created by the developers and writers. I have put so many hours into my adventures as Fogg and Passpartout and I hope I can continue to for a long time.
It's good.
You know what would be great  if you could submit your story and then they print your story in book form!
Stayed up all night playing this! ...which was not good for my health, but it sure was enjoyable! I've never been so enthralled by a game. It's a new adventure every time!
one of my favorite mobile games of all time

I've been kidnapped by nuns, I've successfully led a mutiny, I've survived a shipwreck and I've been caught in the middle of a revolution. This is as close to everything i ever want in a book-game that it can get. The story is never really repeating itself and the events that follow from your choices are beautifully written. It's fun to buy various items from different cities, to sell for a profit, to save as souvenirs or to unlock different paths in the game. The story is really only built around the vallet, Passepartout, and his master becomes a smaller or bigger part depending on how much you want him to be involved. 4.99 out of 5!

Our only issue was playing landscape - markets made it impossible to see your own suitcases and items.

I'm left feeling a little Meh after playing it twice. I managed to get around the world in 56 days on the second try, but noticed that the events on routes I'd done the first time around were the same, and the routes discovered by exploring/buying a timetable are also the same. A proper replayable RPG should have random events and random routes and there are plenty of free ones out there which do this. This, one the other hand, has fixed events and fixed routes, it's just a question of which ones reveal themselves to you. So ... Â£3 isn't much, but there are better games out there which cost less/are free/are in beta (!)
What an incredible game! The world building is fantastic. Well worth the price of entry for this adventure.

Love this game. I have the PC version as well, but love having it on mobile too, for when I need to kill some time! I love that the story is different every time, and that new ports open up each time you play. I wish there was a route through the South Pole!

I've always been a fan of the Jules Verne classic since I read the book as a boy. So was really excited to see this game. It is beautifully written with a lot of decision making involved to complete the journey. The point is no matter how many times you finish it, there is still another way to go around the world. Smooth graphical play with a nice soundtrack. You just have to get used to the reading of the story of the journey which may not be for some.   Delightful game to pass hours away without notice.
Yay great game very immersive. Play it with the soundtrack if possible. Beautiful simple yet elegant

Android M changed the way external storage worked and this has broken the game. Refuses to download because it thinks there's no SD card. Until then I was enjoying it.

As a hardcore bibliophile & former bookseller for Barnes & Noble Booksellers, this app in BEYOND AMAZING! It is a technologically adcanced throwback to the "Choose Your Own Adventure" books I read as a small boy with a HUGE imagination, in the Late 1980s. Kudos to the creators & every single artisan who make this action-packed adventure possible. Totally worth every penny!

Easily the best mobile game I have played - the writing is delightful and witty. We failed to win the wager on our first try, but the story was completely satisfying - mutinies, airship pirates, mysterious inventors - and I cannot wait to try again.

Hands down my favorite mobile game. Endless replay ability. Devs constantly updating. Beautiful story. Challenging gameplay. Awesome.

Compelling story, detailed characters and endless replayability. Loved it.   A few bugs & niggles, though - after first closing and reopening the game, Fogg's heart meter remained stuck at 100 for the rest of the game. The text in conversations is unscrollable and so if too long became unreadable on my 4.5" screen. Also, looking around on the globe view was quite difficult to control. If there's some easy way to return to current city view from globe view, it's not at all obvious, making doing this a bit of a pain.  Even with these minor issues, I still love the heck out of this game. <333  HTC Desire 320, Android 4.4.2 (KitKat).
80 Days is a Storytelling Gem. A well crafted game that uses simple mechanics and a CYOA concept to offer the joy of racing around the world while living through unique and engaging situations.
I became an opium addicted-fire spitting-heroic-taxi stealing man with 36000 in my pocket

A wonderful, charming, beautifully written interactive story which will have you circumnavigating a steam-punk globe in less than 80 days! (Hopefully). This game is a cut above the rest and I'm very happy with it. The gameplay is hard to describe; a mix of interactive fiction, resource management, roleplaying and strategy. Easily one of the best games for androids, humans and automations alike. Well worth the money and highly recommended. 5*
Hands down the best android game I've played.  This game is so immersive, I missed my bus stop on my way to work, ...and I'm not even mad.

content: A great game, I've played it through a few times because you can take many different options. Only two criticisms really, the first of which is the luggage interface, which is very clunky and slow, annoying when you're in a hurry. Secondly it absolutely destroys your battery, despite being a mainly text based adventure. Smacks of programming issues.

Got stuck in infinite loop. Tried to sleep until day 80, but for some reason the game didn't end there. Also unintentionally unlikable main characters and uninteresting exploration outcomes (all you get is route info or info on what you can sell where). Most of the route info is meaningless unless you've got an atlas besides you, since figuring out the big map is both bothersome and stressing due to the other players' markers moving and the time ticking away.
A most fantastic tour through a steam punk enhanced 1872, the writing is more evocative and endering than any other game of its like. Play this game!

content: Nowadays, all that games do is either offer fast-paced repetitive gameplay or put you on a very simple mechanic and raise the difficulty to keep you hooked (whilst bombarding you with in-game purchases).  80 Days, in contrast, tells a STORY, and does it with great elegance. Fiction has originated , in the beginning of human history, from just telling stories, and far too often we forget how important they are for us (the story is the first thing to get cut from games and movies...).  Inkle Studios took the well-known Verne novel, gave it a little spin by adding steampunk elements, designed it with a modern, simple, yet beautiful visual interface, used the obvious "race with time" mechanics mixed with the interactive storytelling elements of the "Choose your own adventure!" books, and wrote a superb score for it. (When the intro reached the "... he was a gambling man" caption part, where the globe starts spinning and the music starts up, it gave me the chills!) The result is a smooth and absolutely enchanting gaming experience.  I wish Inkle Studios great success on the market - shall they present us with many more great games!  Cheers, AndrÃ¡s from Hungary.
Engaging, and nearly infinitely replayable.
Took a little time to getting around to playing the game.
The game is awesome and well worth every penny. It's a shame that not many people have it.

content: This is a very well written, interactive but very story - based game.  It loosely follows the book Around the World in 80 Days where you are trying by various means to circumnavigate the globe in said amount of time.  If you dont get there in 80 days its no matter except a disappointed character.  You can just enjoy the ride.  There are different events you come across, and how you interact with them can determine later events in the the game.  You must also manage money, time, and useful items.

Just not my cup of tea.   I found it tedious, difficult and repetitive and not at all funny.   Otherwise fantastic.
Great visuals, engrossing story, and excellent replayability. Definitely a must-have title for people looking for something a deeper than standard mobile titles.
Game is so entertaining!

The writing is incredibly rich and each journey full of unique scenarios, making it one of the most fun android games to replay. The UI is decent for the most part, but planning your journey and managing items is quite a bit harder than it should be. Still, my most surprisingly delightful android game experience so far.

An entertainingly elegant and overall beautiful experience. Thankfully, the storytelling is superb and the artwork accompanying the prose just as gorgeous and sophisticated. The freedom to plot your own course that leads to eye-opening discoveries, thrilling adventures and amusing banter works perfectly with the classic conceit of having to circumnavigate the world in 80 days to deliver a totally addictive and enjoyable time. Wow. This game is just wow. It is not only a game, it is also a book which is very educative.The culture in cities or in countries are very accurate. replyContent: Sorry to hear it's crashing for you! We did fix a couple of issues affecting the Tab 3 in update 1.0.4, but it looks like you updated already. If you tap Send Feedback in the app after a crash we can investigate and try to get it fixed for you.

content: Fantastic interactive fiction game. The interface is a bit clunky in places but the story of your journey around the world is wonderfully told.

Impeccably presented, deeply satisfying, it would be difficult to imagine a gaming experience closer to perfection. Awesome work once again, Inkle! You are appreciated for what you do.
