The game does feel like it lacks some polish though, I'm especially missing immersive mode and some mis-taps seem to cancel out of conversation early. And finally, I found managing the inventory unresponsive and stressful, it could use a better UI.
This game is extremely detailed, everywhere you go there is a choose your own path that could make the difference between winning the wager and losing. I'd recommend it to anyone

This is a masterful piece of interactive fiction. I enjoyed exploring routes across the world and interacting with unique and interesting characters. I wish the inventory management sections were not timed and tune critical, because the clunky interface for this section made this feel unfair. I would have preferred time to pass per transaction as it does for most other interactions
I enjoyed playing through the different routes you could take around the world and trying to determine all of the secrets the game holds.
Hate the game BORING PURE TIME WASTE this game is for the ones p who have nothing better to do
The writing is really gripping and interesting!

Inkle are quickly becoming one of my favorite studios. Great writing,  clever gameplay and bags of charm to be found in this game. Only gripe is that some of the controls, especially in the inventory and on the world map, feel unintuitive. Keep it coming, inkle!

Amazing integration of well written choose-your-own-adventure type story that has a meaningful impact on the game and is delightful to read. The writing really keeps in-line with Verne's work. Get this game unless you hate geography or reading.  I had no stability/performance issues on my Nexus 10; in fact I was impressed that the game rotated perfectly for landscape/portrait and resumed smoothly when returning from other apps.
This is a great game. Great replay value, interesting, funny and enjoyable
Freezes after 3 or 4 minutes on Asus Memopad 7.  Great concept but I cannot enjoy it

This is a great game. The only problem I'm having is that after the download completed, no shortcut is created, so I have to go to the play store every time I want to open the app up. Anyone know how to fix this?
Love love love it!
Great game but it crashes my tablet - Samsung Galaxy Tab 3 - pretty much every time I try to play it. Although I moved it from SD card to device memory which improved things.
I love this game. It's like a choose your own adventure book, but with so many options! My only problem with it is it kills my battery very quickly
Now how do you go and activate the north pole story?

A fantastic interactive work of fiction. I took a little to get used to the steampunk twist on Verne's world,  but once that happened I was completely immersed in this alternate universe and its wonders.
Excellent game. And the developer was quick to respond personally when I reported a problem with the game. Even updated me via email when a new update was released. Top folk!
Best mobile game I've ever played.
Awesome!
Decisions, luck, wit, management, all in this game
Bought this based on the reviews knowing nothing about it, turns out it's like a choose-your-own-adventure book, which I love!
The adventures you have make the game fun and frustrating. The world of 80 Days is @ a blend of sci-fi, steampunk, and historical.

/But I pressed on only to find out it was indeed not worthy of purchase.../ BUT TO MY SURPRISE IT WAS AN AMAZING GAME, WORTH EVERY CENT AND PULLS YOU IN NEVER TO LET GO, BATTERY DRAINING AND ALL/ I told my master I was sorry for the expense, and found my purchase to be average / It may have been but we ignored it and ventured forth/
One of the best games I have played on any phone! Really good fun and different every time.

One of the best mobile games I've played. Have yourself an adventure around the world. Get shipwrecked in Singapore, stranded in Colombo  and trapped in war torn Mexico.  The splendid steam punk type transport means there are many ways to travel around the world!
Very enjoyable, some interface usability issues, but gameplay is solid.
Great game.  Amazing writing and creativity, lots of replay value.  The interface, especially inventory, is a bit clunky, but that is really my only complaint.  Absolutely worth the price.
So well written. You can play over and over and always get a new story. Highly recommended!  No complaints here.
Would buy again
Great, great. Sure one day I will get back to London in 80. Work your little tricks to get there. Depart and be smart. One day. .. :-)
Refreshing game to play. Loved it
This is mobile gaming done correctly.
Great game to pass the time.
Visually delightful, beautifully written and immersive game. Steam punk twist on the Verne original is nicely done. Thoroughly enjoyable.

Great fun and creative. Game has managed to engage me with each play through. Some of the navigation is awkward, especially around inventory management. In game timer keeps the pace going without feeling too burdensome. Some really clever tricks to keep the game from getting stale, i.e. events change slightly at the start of the game after a few runs. The writing is great except when in "conversation" during travel, which often feels little like conversation at all.
A lovely story game, well deserving of the mountains of praise it has received. New games inspired by 80 days are certain to come.
This is a fantastic choose your own own game. Really replayable and fun romp around the world with a steam punk setting. Would recommend to everyone.
This is such an amazing game totally worth the 5 bucks
It is worth your time.
I love this game, but I would hope that it could save / display every city that I had visited, or route that I took from all previous run through.
Probably one of the best mobile games I've played, and with nothing but a text options. It's the definition of a choose your own adventure.
Not sure if it's just me but the games great however it does drain my phone battery down quite considerably when playing.
I read books & play games all the time, but I never thought that I'll do it at the same time. A 5-star game
Inkle has put out yet another fantastic adventure. Great storyline with believable characters, fair challenges, and excellent replay value. 10/10 would buy again.
Writing and dialogue in most games is amateurish or childish. Not so with 80 days! I really appreciate the quality displayed in this game.
This game is a must buy. At first you may be put off by the lack of direction, but once you begin to understand the game it'll consume you entirely.
It looks great but I can't even open the app I need my money back could of got something else

I hadn't planned on playing through the full 80 days in a single sitting but I was bitten by the travel bug with this fun little game. This title has high replay ability with different routes and I look forward to trying it again.

I am a fan of Willy Fog since I was a child. This adventure text storytelling is for sure entertaining, with its rewriting power. Nonetheless, I'd like to point out that it lacks replayability : Once you've succeeded or failed in the 80 days enterprise, you just don't mind restarting... I had preferred a less challenging and more graphic storybuilding game.
I've never reviewed an app before, but I feel 80 Days deserves it! A nice mix of "Choose-Your-Own-Adventure" style gameplay with fantastic artwork that I've played over and over.

Was recommended this as one of the top mobile games of the year and it did not disappoint I have just completed my first attempt around the world and will try again tomorrow knowing I will have a very different adventure as I try to do so in under 80 days
I bought this game for my mum and I and we both enjoy it greatly
great game, lots of replayability.
What a fun adventure
Awesome!
Stellar game, immersive, and thoroughly enjoyable. Great replay value too
This is such a superbly designed game with fantastic reply value. It is also incredibly hard and I have yet to take the same route or finish the journey in time. Highly recommend it.
Saw the Yogscast livestream it and fell in love with it instantly. Cannot stop playing it!
I just downloaded the game and I had to restart my tablet 10 times in one hour because it froze absolute waste of money
It's a good game but on my 5th play I keep crashing around day 15.
You have to read a lot and the story doesn't seem interesting.
What a charming game.
It's perfect.
This game is like a choose your own adventure book. Everything you do seems to change the story! I've played it over many times!
You can tell this was an I software port and not native to android because it doesn't work.  Definitely want to try it one day.
Gorgeous, well written and absorbing. 80 Days breathes life into the Interactive Fiction genre. I look forward to seeing more from the developers!

I love the style and the marvelous tales. Played one game so far with my girlfriend and was a day off the target date, if only we'd be a little more efficient, investigated that woman's rocket ship, won that boxing match or had that boiler not explode maybe we would have made it. Well worth playing, if there is one thing that makes me sad it's the lack of Google Play Games achievement or leader-board integration but it is but a minor thing.
Beautiful written
Very very buggy, generally i can only play for short periods before it makes my phone freeze or crash.. But very fun when it isn't breaking my phone

The game itself is fairly easy and straightforward to beat in 80 days but I find myself playing over and over again just to visit all the other cities, find the easter eggs, and frankly, just to read more! Brilliantly done.

The dialogue and choices (or lack thereof) grated on me long before the journey's end. Some of it was a bit gay - literally. Which is obviously not for everyone. The zoom out on the map was way too slow - I burned too much in game hours trying to reorientate myself (I got into the habit of snapping back to the city view then going back out into the world map as it was quicker). Also, why no departure time on journeys? Very stupid. I only saw times for journeys that were inactive... but active ones didn't show so you couldn't see how much time you had to burn before departing. The sci-fi story was unexpected but I suppose it makes for a less predictable journey. Overall not too bad a game. Reasonably priced.
The Totalbiscuit army approaches.
Great game. I hope new stories/challenges are upgraded. Also a history of completed and failed attempts would be a fantastic upgrade
Perhaps the best game on Android; I cannot remember the last time I was so charmed. An absolute must for anyone who loves literature,  travelling, and games.
Quite possibly the most boring game I have played
It will not load. I want a refund!

Like on the trail type games, you balance between your boss' approval, your supplies, money and the path you take. The graphics are very crisp and fits the theme. The story is A++. Replayability is infinite!
Great game, can easily lose many hours without realising. Thanks to the developers for getting back to me but the app was installing to the sd card and when switched over to phone memory worked fine
replyContent: Hi Chris, sorry to hear it isn't loading! Can you please send an email to our contact address? There are a few things we can try out to get it working for you.

content: Good idea. Enjoyed what I could. Kept crashing.
Great game get it downloaded u will love it
Nice game. High replayability. You need a good command of english to enjoy it. Only minus - the phone /note 3/ is on "0" mark after 2.30 hours. Generally, costs every paid cent.
This is such a creative and wonderful adventure. It is so absorbing and fascinating!

Once I started playing, I couldn't put it down! Please make a sequel! Minor glitch: if you forget to get your money from the bank and go on a trip, Fogg keeps telling you it will be available during your journey.
Very good world building and story telling. A wonderful journey around a strange earth
Simply fantastic.

I'm usually more of an emulator gamer but I love this game! It's unbelievable how much your choices matter and the crazy situations you can get yourself into. Up there with some of the best rpgs I've played and this isn't even and rpg!
A great combination of choose your own adventure and resource management with terrific writing, it's really a tremendous experience
Really enjoyable.
Engaging  and  fun
Probably the best interactive fiction/visual novel around.
My favourite mobile game I've played yet, however I think a an update created a bug that's force closes the game! Please do try to fix it so people can continue playing it
replyContent: Hi Joey, thanks for the review! Can you please tap Send Feedback in the game, or send an email to our contact address? There are a few things we can try out to get it working for you.

content: Great! Managed 48 days and Â£21,000
Amazing!!!
Pure Awesomeness.

Very detailed, you get an interesting story for 2 bucks, but your just reading and reading and being a servant.  I started twice and got bored of asking people questions and clipping the dudes toenails.  I made it 11 days the second time.  I needed to get to Baghdad, but veered off course and missed a connection I waited a day and a half for after paying 550 to move it up.  Not for me anymore.
A fun well paced adventure! Certainly kept me coming back for more.
Was hoping for a linear, story driven game. Turns out it's that, plus replay value and the fact you can travel as you please! The only thing it could possibly be  missing ils voice acting.
My 12 year old self is happy
It's the best of both worlds.. A good book that I can't put down and a fun game that I can't stop playing. Highly recommended.
Extremely dull
Good
Surprisingly fun
My best so far is 45 days and Â£17,000 up via the North Pole. I intend to explore the world more slowly as well :)
Addicting and Great
Phenomenal. Great work Inkle.
I can't put it down. I like that it's different every time I play!! Well worth it but prepare to lose sleep.
Never was in to text adventures, but this bridges the gap and offers a wonderful experience all your own, and countless playthroughs.
Best game from inkle so far!

Getting rid of the status bar would bring my review up to a five. The status bar chilling out at the top of the screen is a huge distraction for me. Android gives you the tools to get rid of it, use them please!
Worth the money!
More untold tales are waiting to be told. What a an addictive read/play!
Everything about this game is simply terrific. From the art style to the dialogue. A lot of hard work went into this and the people who worked on it deserve a round of applause for this masterpiece!
The best game ever. The story is amazing, i loved the steampunk touches. Will probably be replaying a lot, to see more of this amazing world.

More basic sound and control settings need to be incorporated. And this is such a beautiful game.. It basically has No Entertainment Ceiling. So developers please pay attention to this one and make it endlessly better. So we would want to keep on replaying it again and again and again. Excellent
Just get a black screen on Samsung Galaxy SII running Android 4.0.3.
Truly an adventure you won't soon forget and it's so addictive! Love it.. And each time around is a little bit different.
Packing the suitcases is really annoying. It should be easier to select and move items to the desired suitcase.            Everything else is great about this game.
An absolute masterpiece
GAME.
A beautifully designed and written game, quirky with bags of character. Like one of your favourite books that you get to jump right into. Easy to pick up, no IAP, perfect mobile gaming

my only gripes are (1) no pause or save button (2) this kills the battery (3) weird retro-futuristic vehicles and quirky bits of story [i was teleported across the map, wtf?!?] Still 4 stars and worth the price.
Really well thought through and stylish to boot.

This is nothing short of one of the most engaging and thoughtful video game experiences I've ever had. Not just on mobile, but any platform. An awesome RPG and elegant piece of literature in one, it's the best $5 I've spent in a long time.
It would be nice if when you hit the back button the fame didn't close.
Crashes regularly on Galaxy Tab 3, requiring tablet to be shut down and restarted each time. Shame, as looks like a good game...Update...sadly still crashing even after new version from devs...
replyContent: Apologies! We had a server glitch, it's now fixed.

content: .. but this is a must play! One of the best games I've played... ever. The pacing is really smart (small bits of adventure, mini cliffhangers with a lot of tension building up on the journey), the writing is great and the aesthetics... well it's very beautiful.  I have one little complaint which is that for some reason my game crashes once I complete my journey, on the very last conversation with Fogg. (I understand that I shouldn't have to reset to go around the world again.) Any idea why this is?
beautifully designed and written with almost endless replay value. A brilliant example of what mobile gaming should be.

Needs a bit more work. The game has a tendency of ignoring touch input at times. Switching screen orientation fixes this issue. One major issue I had was taking the airship from Manila to Honolulu, which causes the game to crash and effectively forces you to restart from the beginning.

Game has been working well but surprisingly nearing to the last leg of the race, game unexpectedly starts to freeze and stop. Even after uninstalling and reinstalling, game still freezes. Im using galaxy note edge. Truly2 disappointed in the outcome of this app.
replyContent: Apologies! We had a server glitch, it's now fixed.

content: I played it a little bit and then exited, but everytime I open it now it crashes. I have a Note 3 and will give 5 stars gladly when crashing is fixed.
replyContent: Apologies! We had a server glitch, it's now fixed.

content: You won't regret playing this game.
I am in awe of this game! Good writing, interesting mechanics and great replay value. BUY BUY BUY!

Full of replay value. A strange and good adaptation of the classic novel. Love the artwork. The writing is topnotch. Hope Inkle brings more games to the Android, preferably those that are compatible with a mobile phone and not just on tablets.
Keeps me interested in playing again the next time, no save feature though... But this is one of the few games I paid for. Great job!

Truly. I'll buy everything that comes out from inkle, because I know the games will be worth it. Only... Can we save old progresses? I'd really like to be able to see each of the routes I take. Also, why is it so hard to open your luggage?
If you like reading books, this game is an absolute must. Choose-your-adventure type of game, but so, so creative, innovative and interesting.
Personally I think this sets the mark for most role playing games, not only in pocket form. I was never one for stories but twinned with the adventure and creativity the game is highly enjoyable.

Easily a 5 except for two niggling issues. (A) You can't disable sound so you can listen to your own music while playing, and (B) luggage organization is very fiddly, often closing when it shouldn't and taking several seconds to open. In all other respects this game is a wonderful adventure I can recommend wholeheartedly!
A great game well worth the price of admission.
The developers have clearly put their heart and soul into making this a bug free, well polished adventure game. Worth the price tag easily.  Keep it up guys!
Great game.

I just got kidnapped by a cult in the Indian jungle while riding the mechanical elephant! Another awesome game by Inkle. Have been waiting months for this to come out for Android. Ps. There a bug when using the Market - sometimes you can't move things in and out of your suitcases. I have the Galaxy S4. Pps. Pls hurry up with Sorcery 3! :)

As with every game from inkle, this just oozes quality, charm and polish. An incredible amount of hard work has gone into this. An amazing dynamic story with so much replayability I don't know if I could ever see all the content. The constantly ticking clock gives such a sense of urgency, I tend to make panic decisions! I just love the globe map, though it can be a little fiddly. I haven't made it within 80 days yet, but I have come close! If you love choose-your-own-adventure you can't pass this up!
Amazing
Outstanding adventure game uses the mobile platform beautifully to deliver great old-school text-based CYOA augmented with beautiful art.  I wish there were more like it.

Solved a murder mystery on a crazy boat, boxed a man in america, slept rough in Iceland. Its an excellent game that's constantly throwing cool and interesting storylines at you. Worth every penny and is probably my game of the year, a must buy.
no IAP's, beautiful graphics, so far a nice story telling... there's nothing more you can ask from a game. well worth the money spent on this.
An incredible world and an incredible story
Based on preliminary play, 30 min or so. Also, no issues on software side.
never has a game instilled so much wanderlust in me, or such a sense of adventure!
Can't believe I had to wait for last day of my holiday for this. Will have to cancel Xmas now. Great game.
Thank you guys at inkle. Fantastic piece of work, loved the implementation, really enjoying the game. A real gem and easily worth the price on the door. Completely recommended.

Ever since Sorcery! came along and absolutely blew me away, I've paid close attention to this developer.  As a big gamebook fan, I've really enjoyed seeing how talented devs such as Tin Man so artfully create experiences that are truly immersive and engaging.  Quality presentation is key and, in my opinion, just as important as skillful writing in bringing these apps to life.  Inkle's gamebooks have such a unique, gorgeous style and amazing writing, and in 80 Days they've raised the bar even higher.
This game is outstanding. Even if your not in to this genre of game, still play the heck out of 80 DAYS. Its a masterpiece. Absolute perfection in my book inkle. Bring on more DLC!!!
It's finally here! The game is beautiful, just as I was expected to see. Can't wait to finish this. :-D
I've been waiting months for this game to come out on Android, and it's finally here. 80 Days is a fantastic journey pretty much unparalleled in the current medium. I highly recommend it to everyone.
Love the idea of it and production values are good. I was expecting deeper story instead of very short snippets for each city.  With that in mind, I prefer Sorcery but don't let that stop you.
Been loving this game on ios. Cant wait to see the new content!
I'm so glad this came to android, in my opinion this is the best game for mobile devices
A beautifully put together steampunk journey.  Highly recommended!
Super nice!
I'd wager that you'll enjoy this.
Amazing game! Not usually a fan of steam punk, atleast not in mobile games. This game takes it to the next level. I look forward to playing this nonstop for the next few weeks!
